_border="on" circle_border_color="#ffffff" icon_placement="top" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center"]<p>Completely "plug &amp; play". No installation required</p>[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Open Source" url_new_window="off" use_icon="on" font_icon="" icon_color="#ed1c24" use_circle="off" circle_color="#ffffff" use_circle_border="on" circle_border_color="#ffffff" icon_placement="top" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center"]<p>You can hack it into whatever you may want</p>[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fullwidth="off" specialty="off"][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="1_2"][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left"]<p>We believe that everyone should have access to this technology. So we made smart homes easy.</p><p>Adding a new device is as simple as pluging it in and activate it.</p><p><b> </b></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fullwidth="off" specialty="off"][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_cta admin_label="It''s low cost" title="It''s low cost" use_background_color="on" background_color="#ffffff" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center"]<p>Let me show you how inexpensive it is.</p><p>All devices in the house are connected together through the  house’s existing wiring. And the network connects to the internet through our gateway. This reduces the overall complexity of the system. Your devices no longer need to have wi-fi or bluetooth, hence diminishing its cost.</p>[/et_pb_cta][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image" src="http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/diagrama-plc.png" show_in_lightbox="off" url_new_window="off" animation="left" /][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fullwidth="off" specialty="off"][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_slider admin_label="Slider" show_arrows="on" show_pagination="on" auto="on" parallax="off" auto_speed="5000"][et_pb_slide background_image="http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/belerofonte.jpg" background_color="#ffffff" alignment="center" background_layout="dark"]<p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>[/et_pb_slide][et_pb_slide background_image="http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/belerofonte-2.jpg" background_color="#ffffff" alignment="center" background_layout="dark" /][et_pb_slide background_image="http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/belerofonte-3.jpg" background_color="#ffffff" alignment="center" background_layout="dark" /][et_pb_slide background_image="http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/belerofonte-4.jpg" background_color="#ffffff" alignment="center" background_layout="dark" /][/et_pb_slider][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_cta admin_label="Open source" title="Don''t wait for it, Do It Yourself!" use_background_color="on" background_color="#ffffff" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center"]<p>Here is where stuff gets techie. For those who love to go a little further we have developed a shield for arduino and Raspberry pi. Use it with our open SDK and develop your own gadgets with full PLC connectivity.</p><p>We’re looking forward to seeing what the community can do with this. It’s the power of PLC at your fingertips.</p><p><a href="http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/opensource-logo.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-221" src="http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/opensource-logo.png" alt="" width="320" height="84" /></a></p>[/et_pb_cta][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fullwidth="on" specialty="off" background_color="#ed1c24" inner_shadow="off" parallax="off" parallax_method="css"][et_pb_fullwidth_header admin_label="Team Slider" title="The Team" background_layout="dark" text_orientation="center" /][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fu