(459, 2, '2014-12-24 12:14:50', '2014-12-24 12:14:50', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/domocracy_zombie_post_zombies.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-439 alignright" src="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/domocracy_zombie_post_zombies.jpg" alt="domocracy_zombie_post_zombies" width="300" height="288" /></a></p>\r\nNew year, new life... but... Zombies! What will you do if this coming year a Z infestation arises? We don''t want you to be afraid... But is your house ready? If it’s not, sorry... you''re dead... But luckily you are not like everyone else! You are a DOMOcrat!\r\n\r\nWe hope It will never happen but if this new age appears, we want to give you some tips about how to fight and emerge victorious with Domocracy!\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/close-doors.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-447 " src="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/close-doors.png" alt="blog_zombie_close_doors" width="391" height="39" /></a>\r\n\r\nThere''s no time to think! You need to react fast, they are coming and you don''t want a pretty gore party inside home... Secure your house locking every door, from everywhere, with a simple tap!\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-448 " src="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/moth.png" alt="blog_zombie_moth" width="292" height="35" />\r\n\r\nEverybody knows the analogy between zombies and insects, both love light ♥... Distract them flashing lights and turning on your radio while you are running away.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-445 " src="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/ninja.png" alt="blog_zombie_ninja" width="207" height="42" />\r\n\r\nMaybe you are one of those who prefer a stealthy style... Turn off your porch''s light without going out and keep <i>the rottens</i> away.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-446 " src="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/bio.png" alt="blog_zombie_bio" width="185" height="39" />\r\n\r\nAnd what about using the garage door as scalpel. Kill some zombies closing the door and splinting zombies as frogs in a high-school biology class.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/usa_garage_door.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-435" src="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/usa_garage_door.jpg" alt="usa_garage_door" width="515" height="342" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-449 " src="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/boom.png" alt="blog_zombie_boom" width="165" height="45" />\r\n\r\n<img class="size-medium wp-image-440 alignright" src="http://www.domocracytech.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/domocracy_blog_post_zombie_flyback_transformer_arc-300x200.jpg" alt="Spark Maker" width="300" height="200" />\r\n\r\nIf you have a second house away from the city. It may be the time to think about moving to the suburbs. But not before making some beautyfull fireworks show. It''s easy,\r\n\r\nStep 1: Make a spark maker\r\n\r\nStep 2: Leave your (gas/propane) tank on\r\n\r\nStep 3: Prepare your car and drive away.\r\n\r\nStep 4: Turn on the spark maker with our mobile application and have fun with the fireworks.\r\n<p style="text-align: right;"><strong>WARNING! Take care, and be sure to be away enough from the explosion.</strong></p>\r\nOh! And don’t forget to turn on the heater, remotely with your smartphone obviously, on the other house. Winter has come!', 'Zombies', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '432-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-24 12:14:50', '2014-12-24 12:14:50', '', 432, 'http://www.domocracytech.com/432-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(460, 5, '2014-12-24 12:44:13', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'All of us that are up to date as far as gaming is concerned blindly know that we are facing systems that need constant updating of software. Whether it is to fix bugs or to address security holes, new consoles coninuously surprise the user with the obligation to download a large amount of  information.\r\n\r\nThe problem comes when many of us arrive at home from our jobs and want to take a quick play and console keeps us from playing until the update is performed. We can say that it is possible to continue without running the patching process, but if the game in question makes use of online functionality, it is essential to have the software up to date. Good examples are recent launches as Destiny, The Crew or Call of Duty: Advanced Warfare, which  are completely built around the online experience. Similarly, if it’s the console itself that needs updating, we face the same situation to playonline.\r\n\r\nAll this would be no problem if the downloads were light, but it is usually the case that we can find several gigabytes to download, which may become very frustrating if our time is limited. It is true that the new machines are trained to automatically download patches they come out, but we must connect the console. In this regard, having the console in an automated home environment has important advantages.\r\n\r\nI give you an example. The guy writing this post gets out his work with the idea of playing a while before it comes time to make dinner, but fears that this situation can not be carried out based on a more than likely download (roughly every other day comes a new patch for my library of games). So from my Smarphone, I decide to turn on the console on my way home, about 45 minutes before arrival... more than enough to make a major patch down time. So, when he comes home, everything will be ready and prepared to grab the pad and get to save the galaxy.', 'Updating your system', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2014-12-24 12:44:13', '2014-12-24 12:44:13', '', 0, 'http://www.domocracytech.com/?p=460', 0, 'post', '', 0),
